text: Chlanidota signeyana is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae, the true whelks. It was described by Harold Powell in 1951. ==Description== ==Distribution== This marine species occurs off Timor. ==References== * Lamy, Ed., 1910.
